<p><abbr title="γιγνώσκων, εἶδος, ὄντος, φαίνων">GEOF</abbr> is an open source sci-fi game engine designed to create an immersive and imaginative setting from naturalistic simulations.</p>
<p>Currently it’s able to store information in a <a href="https://github.com/G-E-O-F/peels#readme" target="_blank">geodesic sphere</a> and determine <a href="https://github.com/G-E-O-F/warmth#readme" target="_blank">how much sunlight is received</a> by any location on a stellar body. You can see the latter in action here, visualizing the sun's radiation on Earth at this moment.</p>
<p>Planned features include geography/erosion, climate, economic markets, politics, espionage, and theaters of war using simulations used by researchers of those phenomena. Ultimately GEOF should offer a framework for writers and creative artists to build compelling stories with.</p>